<TITLE> SAARC secretary-general praises Bangladesh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 13 (bdnews24.com)  SAARC secretary-general Lyonpo Chenkyab Dorji Sunday praised Bangladesh for its efforts to broaden cooperation in the regional grouping. "Bangladesh is deeply committed to expanding regional cooperation," Dorji said to journalists after meeting foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury. Doriji is in Dhaka as part of his tour of the member countries at the end of his three-year stint. Indian diplomat Sheel Kant Sharma is scheduled to replace him as secretary general soon. "I've begun my farewell calls from Dhaka, for Bangladesh is the birth place of SAARC," he said. Dorji, a Bhutanese bureaucrat, was appointed secretary-general in 2005. bdn
